                        <br><br>
                        Some quick tips:</p>
                        <ol>
                         <li>Check your email for the first day agenda:.</li>

                        <li>Prepare your questions and expectations: Think about what you want to learn, achieve, and contribute in your new role.</li>

                        <li>Pack your essentials: Make sure you have everything you need for your first day, such as your ID</li>

                        <li>Arrive on time and dress appropriately: Plan to arrive at least 15 minutes before the start of the orientation events.</li>

